managementserver

Interface ISubject<TYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    TYPE - The type of the objects that an IObserver will be notified about
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ISubjectManagementServer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ManagementServer

    public interface ISubject<TYPE>
    This interface is part of the Observer pattern and specifies the behavior of the subject. It basically allows another objects (the IObserver)s to retrieve changes from the subject.

    This interface is generic and has a single typeparameter. In essence, this typeparameter specifies the type of the objects that an IObserver will be notified about.

    Author:
    OOP

        Registers an IObserver in the ISubject.
        Parameters:
        obs - the IObserver that should be registered
        Returns:

      • unregister

        boolean unregister(IObserver obs)
        Unregisters the IObserver in the ISubject. In this case notifications are disabled (via the method IObserver.deactivateNotifications(ISubjectManagementServer)).
        Parameters:
        obs - the IObserver that should be unregistered
        Returns:
        boolean TRUE if the passed argument is not NULL and registered at the ISubject. Otherwise FALSE.
